{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make a law that traffic light sensors should recognise the presence of bicycles.",
        "additional_details": "Fitting adequate sensors that detect the presence if bicycles at traffic lights would at the very least remove the alarm and terror from a cyclist suddenly and unexpectedly facing over a ton of steel driving toward them, head on; or more importantly, possibly save lives.",
        "background": "Make it law that temporary and fixed traffic lights must have adequate sensors that also detect the presence of solo bicycles.\r\nAt the moment many are sensing the arrival of an oncoming motor vehical and changing lights whilst cyclists are still going through, risking a head-on collision!",
